On the extensive ground of opinion I
confess that the general structure
and appearances of the primitive
Rocks offer very few facts favourable
to [underline]either Hypothesis[/underline].-
For as I have [underline]already said[/underline] their
principal materials are neither fusible
by fire nor soluble in water - 
As yet no particle of pure [chemical]chemical_102|Quartz[/chemical]
has been rendered fluid by the

[page]43|MS-DAVY-11606-000-00043|dnp16f41pp|94870105[/page]
strongest Heat of our furnaces assisted by
the most powerful [underline]effects of Air[/underline]:
And it is therefore scarcely possible to
believe that mountains of [underline]this stone[/underline] more 
than a mile in perpendicular height
and many miles in circumference can
have been rendered fluid by subterraneous
Heat excited without the [underline]access of Air[/underline]
and supposed to act even immediately
[underline]beneath the water of the Ocean[/underline].
There is indeed another strong argumen
[underline]against the primitive[/underline] Rocks having been
formed by fire from the remains of
former Continents and [underline]islands[/underline].

