our latitude it is about five thousand
feet [place]place_995|[underline]Ben Nevis[/underline][/place] being [underline]very little within[/underline]
the limits of constant [underline]ice[/underline] -
It is in consequence of this [underline]circumstance[/underline]
that mountain chains affect in a high
degree the temperature of the climate
in which they exist -
In the summer currents of cold air are
continually flowing down [underline]their sides[/underline]
which mitigate the burning heat of the
season

